  = 96801â96898 |area_code = 808 |website = [http://www.honolulu.gov/
  www.honolulu.gov] |footnotes = }} 'Honolulu County' (officially known as the
  'City and County of Honolulu', formerly 'Oahu County') is a consolidated
  cityâcounty located in the U.S. state of Hawaii. The City and County includes
  both the City of Honolulu (the state's largest city and state capital) and the
  rest of the island of O{{okina}}ahu, as well as several minor outlying
  islands, including all of the Northwestern Hawaiian Islands (islands beyond
  Niihau) except Midway Atoll.

The consolidated city-county was established in the city charter adopted in 1907
and accepted by the Legislature of the Territory of Hawai{{okina}}i. {{cite web
  | coauthors = City and County of Honolulu title = About the City and County of
  | Honolulu publisher = City and County of Honolulu url =
  | http://www.honolulu.gov/cchnl.htm#city format = Government website
  | accessdate = 2008-01-27}} As a municipal corporation and jurisdiction
  | it manages aspects of government traditionally exercised by both
  | municipalities and counties in the rest of the United States.

The population of Honolulu County at the 2010 Census was 953,207, making it the
tenth-largest municipality in the United States. {{cite web
  | coauthors = Marchex, Inc. title = Hawaii Fast Facts and Trivia publisher =
  | Marchex, Inc. url = http://www.50states.com/facts/hawaii.htm format =
  | Commercial website accessdate = 2008-01-27}} Because of Hawaii's
  | municipal structure, the United States Census
  | Bureau still divides Honolulu County into several census-designated places
  | for statistical purposes, despite the fact that it is the only incorporated
  | area in the state.

The current mayor of Honolulu County is Kirk Caldwell, who reclaimed the job
from the person who defeated him in a 2010 special election, Peter Carlisle, in
2013. The county motto is Haaheo No O Honolulu (Honolulu
Pride). "[http://www.honolulu.gov/refs/menu/ecodev/sistercities/events.htm
Events, Official Web Site for The City and County of Honolulu]." City and County
of Honolulu. Accessed October 14, 2008.
